\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 50.           Xanthium}             L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By D. Löve.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Annual herbs. Leaves alternate, entire or variously lobed. Capitula solitary or in axillary clusters, unisexual, the male above the female. Male capitula subglobose; involucral bracts in 1 row; receptacle cylindrical, with scales; florets numerous; stamens 5; anthers free and hooked at apex; filaments connate; style and ovary rudimentary. Female capitula ovoid; involucral bracts in 2 rows, the outer small, free, the inner connate, coriaceous, prickly, ending in 2 (rarely 1) beaks and forming a 2-locular structure containing 2 florets; corolla absent; styles exserted through a hole on the inside of the beak near its base. Achenes ovoid; pappus absent.
\par

\par

